WEBVTT

05:16.983 --> 05:18.901
<i>So, did Mai…</i>

05:19.652 --> 05:20.653
actually die?

05:22.071 --> 05:24.489
Right now, we should be worried
about the head of the family.

05:24.490 --> 05:26.950
And besides, the one
who’s on the brink of death is Maki.

05:26.951 --> 05:29.953
Oh, really? Whatever.

05:29.954 --> 05:32.664
Maki is a pretty girl,
sure, but she’s no good.

05:32.665 --> 05:35.000
She can’t let a man take the lead.

05:35.001 --> 05:38.963
A woman who can’t be submissive
should get stabbed in the back and die.

05:39.964 --> 05:42.716
In that respect, Mai is admirable.

05:42.717 --> 05:44.761
NAOYA ZEN'IN
SPECIAL GRADE 1 SORCERER

05:45.428 --> 05:48.805
She has the same face as Maki,
and the same chest too.

05:48.806 --> 05:53.477
She puts on a tough front,
but she truly understands she’s a woman.

05:53.478 --> 05:57.064
You’re late. What were you doing?

05:57.065 --> 06:00.609
While your own father is wandering
around the mountain pass, half dead!

06:00.610 --> 06:02.194
Sorry about that.

06:02.195 --> 06:05.031
But it doesn’t really matter, does it?
Whether I show up or not.

06:05.782 --> 06:08.701
The next head of the Zen'in clan
is me anyway.

06:09.827 --> 06:13.039
All my older brothers are useless.

06:13.623 --> 06:15.040
Uncle.

06:15.041 --> 06:17.334
Even you, his younger brother,
amount to nothing.

06:17.335 --> 06:19.461
And your daughter is out of the question.

06:19.462 --> 06:21.380
Jinichi, you know…

06:24.008 --> 06:26.093
Your face is the problem.

06:26.094 --> 06:28.721
If only it had been
the other way around with Toji.

06:32.141 --> 06:34.893
OGI ZEN'IN
SPECIAL GRADE 1 SORCERER

06:34.894 --> 06:36.478
JINICHI ZEN'IN
SPECIAL GRADE 1 SORCERER

06:36.479 --> 06:39.106
Dad is wandering around
the mountain pass, you know.

06:39.107 --> 06:41.400
Cut him some slack.

06:42.068 --> 06:44.153
Everyone is here.

06:46.405 --> 06:49.199
Just moments ago,
the head of the Zen'in clan,

06:49.200 --> 06:53.037
Lord Naobito Zen'in, passed away.

06:56.499 --> 07:01.253
The will is in my custody.

07:01.254 --> 07:04.757
In accordance with
Lord Naobito’s final wishes,

07:05.341 --> 07:06.968
Ogi Zen'in,

07:07.552 --> 07:09.678
Jinichi Zen'in,

07:09.679 --> 07:11.931
and Naoya Zen'in…

07:12.557 --> 07:14.599
Once all three of you are present,

07:14.600 --> 07:17.895
I am instructed to convey this to you.

07:19.105 --> 07:22.942
If there are no objections,
I will read the will.

07:29.615 --> 07:33.410
First. Naoya Zen'in shall be appointed

07:33.411 --> 07:35.455
27th head of the Zen'in clan.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.622
Second.

07:37.623 --> 07:40.041
All assets, including cursed tools

07:40.042 --> 07:42.836
stored in the Tokyo Jujutsu High vault

07:42.837 --> 07:45.840
and the Zen'in clan vault,
shall be inherited by Naoya.

07:46.424 --> 07:47.799
With the approval of either

07:47.800 --> 07:51.721
Ogi Zen'in or Jinichi Zen'in,

07:52.555 --> 07:55.516
Naoya shall assume control
and manage said assets.

07:57.185 --> 07:59.353
- Well, fine then.
- However,

08:00.396 --> 08:04.524
if, for any reason, Satoru Gojo dies

08:04.525 --> 08:07.569
or loses the ability
to act of his own will,

08:07.570 --> 08:11.239
the pledge made with Toji Fushiguro
shall be carried out.

08:11.240 --> 08:14.326
Megumi Fushiguro shall be taken in
by the Zen'in clan,

08:14.327 --> 08:17.454
and appointed head of the Zen'in clan.

08:17.455 --> 08:21.083
All assets shall be transferred.

08:23.586 --> 08:27.672
No. That won’t do.
Those two are spineless.

08:27.673 --> 08:29.883
A kid they barely know
can become the head.

08:29.884 --> 08:31.886
As long as it’s not me,
they won't do a thing.

08:33.763 --> 08:36.348
So where is Megumi right now?
What is he doing?

08:36.349 --> 08:38.934
I don’t know the details,
but I hear he’s in Tokyo,

08:38.935 --> 08:41.853
assigned to the search for Yuji Itadori.

08:41.854 --> 08:43.480
Who’s that?

08:43.481 --> 08:45.149
The vessel of Sukuna.

08:45.816 --> 08:48.109
Then pass this on to the higher-ups.

08:48.110 --> 08:51.571
- Naoya Zen'in will kill Sukuna’s vessel.
- What?

08:51.572 --> 08:54.908
Megumi is with the vessel
of Sukuna, right?

08:54.909 --> 08:56.536
I’ll kill them both at once.

08:57.745 --> 08:59.413
Right now, Tokyo is a demon-infested hell.

09:00.248 --> 09:02.792
It doesn’t matter when or how people die.

09:03.876 --> 09:07.296
Once they’re dead,
everything else will work itself out.

09:10.508 --> 09:13.052
I’m the head of the Zen'in clan.

09:22.436 --> 09:23.813
<i>Die.</i>

09:24.981 --> 09:26.231
<i>- Wait!
- Again…</i>

09:26.232 --> 09:27.775
<i>- Itadori.
- Itadori.</i>

09:28.526 --> 09:29.860
<i>What will you do?</i>

09:54.760 --> 09:55.886
Yuji.

09:57.263 --> 09:58.681
How are your injuries?

09:59.890 --> 10:04.061
Other than taking a hit, I’m mostly fine.

10:05.313 --> 10:07.939
It’s probably Sukuna’s influence.

10:07.940 --> 10:10.651
I can feel his power growing.

10:11.986 --> 10:15.071
Yuji. Don’t worry about me.

10:15.072 --> 10:17.657
You can go back to Jujutsu High.

10:17.658 --> 10:20.745
I want to recover Shoso's bodies anyway.

10:22.371 --> 10:23.581
I’m not holding back.

10:24.415 --> 10:27.084
This isn’t about
whether I want to go back.

10:27.668 --> 10:30.880
Sukuna is using Fushiguro
to plan something.

10:31.631 --> 10:33.381
And…

10:33.382 --> 10:35.509
I've killed a lot of people.

10:36.010 --> 10:40.097
<i>What if the person you saved
ends up killing someone someday?</i>

10:41.265 --> 10:44.435
I can’t be with everyone anymore.

10:45.269 --> 10:49.314
Are you really okay with this, Choso?
I killed your brothers too.

10:49.315 --> 10:53.401
It’s fine. That was an accident.
If Eso and Kechizu

10:53.402 --> 10:56.488
were in my position,
they would’ve done the same.

10:56.489 --> 11:00.951
It's not about forgiving or not forgiving.
That’s what it means to be brothers.

11:04.330 --> 11:08.042
Let’s go. For now, we just need
to reduce the number of curses.

13:00.404 --> 13:01.655
Mother!

13:08.829 --> 13:09.788
Yuji.

13:22.426 --> 13:24.427
<i>Incredible.</i>

13:24.428 --> 13:27.764
<i>When you fought me,
you struck me as purely powerful.</i>

13:27.765 --> 13:30.475
<i>Now, there’s a delicacy to it as well.</i>

13:30.476 --> 13:34.480
<i>Flawless cursed energy control,
strength on an entirely different level.</i>

13:37.024 --> 13:39.108
<i>A true demon god.</i>

13:39.109 --> 13:42.446
<i>And to think
you’re still not fully recovered.</i>

13:43.822 --> 13:46.075
As expected. That’s my little brother.

13:46.659 --> 13:47.910
You’re still saying that?

13:49.119 --> 13:50.870
I’ll say it as many times as it takes.

13:50.871 --> 13:53.832
Remember. It must have happened.

13:57.127 --> 13:58.671
Your father’s forehead too…

13:59.255 --> 14:00.589
The stitches…

14:02.967 --> 14:05.176
Megumi is not here, huh?

14:05.177 --> 14:06.678
Am I the first to arrive?

14:06.679 --> 14:09.514
Does that even happen? Are they that slow?

14:09.515 --> 14:11.599
Who’s this guy?

14:11.600 --> 14:13.435
Did he just mention Fushiguro?

14:14.019 --> 14:18.399
What are you two doing? You stand out
too much. Not trying to run away?

14:19.066 --> 14:20.400
Run?

14:20.401 --> 14:21.694
What, you didn’t know?

14:22.403 --> 14:24.737
You’ve been sentenced to death,

14:24.738 --> 14:27.324
now that Satoru's protection is gone.

14:30.369 --> 14:31.786
Gojo used to allow

14:31.787 --> 14:35.498
his so-called selfishness,
and saved a lot of jujutsu sorcerers!

14:35.499 --> 14:38.251
The one I’m after is Megumi,

14:38.252 --> 14:41.337
so honestly, I don’t really care
whether you live or die.

14:41.338 --> 14:43.590
But letting you dart around
would be annoying too,

14:43.591 --> 14:46.051
so I figured I would break a leg or two
while I’m at it.

14:46.635 --> 14:48.636
What do you want with Fushiguro?

14:48.637 --> 14:51.055
I want him dead.

14:51.056 --> 14:54.559
Before that, it would help
if he signed something for me.

14:54.560 --> 14:57.313
Megumi has been
looking for you, apparently.

15:09.408 --> 15:10.618
What?

15:13.954 --> 15:14.955
PARKING AREA

15:17.416 --> 15:20.586
He’s fast, sure, but something feels off.

15:21.170 --> 15:22.712
It’s probably a technique.

15:22.713 --> 15:25.048
You’re better than I thought.

15:25.049 --> 15:26.967
Honestly, I underestimated you.

15:27.927 --> 15:31.472
<i>I get the vessel,
but what’s the one next to him?</i>

15:32.056 --> 15:34.433
<i>Let’s crank it up a bit more, shall we?</i>

15:40.606 --> 15:44.985
<i>Mr. Gojo! No!
Something even more unsettling…</i>

15:52.117 --> 15:54.870
What? He's not alone.

16:01.085 --> 16:03.754
- Who is that?
- <i>Whoever it is, their objective is…</i>

16:04.338 --> 16:06.757
Who’s going to kill Itadori? What?

16:07.841 --> 16:10.511
<i>So, he's Yuji’s executioner after all.</i>

16:18.727 --> 16:21.146
Hold on a second. I’m on your side.

16:22.022 --> 16:23.606
You’re Okkotsu, right?

16:23.607 --> 16:25.358
<i>Okkotsu…</i>

16:25.359 --> 16:27.568
<i>The second-year Fushiguro mentioned…</i>

16:27.569 --> 16:30.613
<i>The special-grade sorcerer,
same as Mr. Gojo.</i>

16:30.614 --> 16:31.864
And you are?

16:31.865 --> 16:35.410
Naoya Zen'in. Maki's cousin.

16:35.411 --> 16:37.996
Just like you,
I’ve been told to kill Itadori.

16:37.997 --> 16:39.790
- Let's go, Yuji.
- Relax.

16:40.499 --> 16:42.250
I won’t interfere.

16:42.251 --> 16:45.169
The blond one is a speed type with tricks.

16:45.170 --> 16:49.007
A chase with him won’t end well.
I’ll hold him off.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.383
Are you sure?

16:50.384 --> 16:53.261
In return, if you kill Itadori,

16:53.262 --> 16:56.389
could you keep quiet about it
to the bosses for a while?

16:56.390 --> 16:58.308
I want to meet someone. He’s good bait.

16:58.934 --> 17:02.979
The one being targeted is you, Yuji.

17:02.980 --> 17:04.272
Black hair…

17:04.273 --> 17:07.525
Focus only on escaping from Okkotsu.

17:07.526 --> 17:11.529
He’s the same type as Satoru Gojo.
If you fight him, you’ll die.

17:11.530 --> 17:15.783
<i>Should’ve kept quiet about Megumi.
That sent a chill down my spine.</i>

17:15.784 --> 17:18.369
<i>A proposal that keeps Yuji
from fighting a sorcerer,</i>

17:18.370 --> 17:21.582
<i>and keeps me
from feeling indebted to humans…</i>

17:22.541 --> 17:24.542
<i>What a hassle.</i>

17:24.543 --> 17:26.419
We’ll meet up at yesterday’s location.

17:26.420 --> 17:29.547
Sure. I’ll leave that side to you.

17:29.548 --> 17:30.799
Got it!

17:32.926 --> 17:35.721
<i>So fast! And this is him
when carrying a drawn blade?</i>

17:37.931 --> 17:41.059
<i>He's fast. I was planning to crush him
right at the start.</i>

17:41.060 --> 17:45.564
<i>Damn it. So he saw through my plan
to block Okkotsu’s path?</i>

17:46.148 --> 17:50.109
I saw it earlier.
Blood Manipulation, right?

17:50.110 --> 17:53.571
No idea why you have it,

17:53.572 --> 17:56.199
but aside from Piercing Blood,
it’s not that scary.

17:56.200 --> 17:58.951
And to use Piercing Blood,
you need to charge with Convergence.

17:58.952 --> 18:00.369
That takes time.

18:00.370 --> 18:02.997
You get the rest
without me saying it, right?

18:02.998 --> 18:05.042
Checkmate. You’re dead.

18:05.667 --> 18:07.168
Worry about yourself.

18:07.169 --> 18:09.754
Do you really think
you can lay a hand on my brother

18:09.755 --> 18:12.633
and walk away alive?

18:33.529 --> 18:36.072
<i>I was sure I cut him…</i>

18:36.073 --> 18:37.699
<i>Just like Maki.</i>

18:59.471 --> 19:03.307
Surprised?
I don’t look like a power type, do I?

19:03.308 --> 19:05.227
<i>Even without power,</i>

19:05.811 --> 19:07.854
<i>that cursed energy output is insane!</i>

19:07.855 --> 19:09.939
I actually am on the weaker side.

19:09.940 --> 19:13.359
<i>He compensates for the lack of power
by reinforcing himself with cursed energy.</i>

19:13.360 --> 19:16.612
<i>Everyone does it, but when he does it…</i>

19:16.613 --> 19:17.865
He’s the complete opposite of me.

19:20.826 --> 19:25.455
You noticed? I’ve got more cursed energy
than Mr. Gojo.

19:26.790 --> 19:29.292
<i>But Mr. Gojo has the Six Eyes,</i>

19:29.293 --> 19:32.128
<i>so when he activates techniques,</i>

19:32.129 --> 19:33.755
<i>his energy loss is practically zero.</i>

19:34.715 --> 19:37.259
<i>In terms of performance,
he’s still number one.</i>

19:38.302 --> 19:41.805
I might run out of cursed energy,
but he never does.

19:43.140 --> 19:45.058
And now, I'm done talking.

19:50.689 --> 19:53.065
<i>- Damn it.
- The better the sorcerer,</i>

19:53.066 --> 19:55.401
<i>the harder it is to read
their flow of cursed energy.</i>

19:55.402 --> 19:57.195
<i>For a different reason than you.</i>

19:57.196 --> 19:58.946
<i>That means top-tier sorcerers</i>

19:58.947 --> 20:00.698
<i>have more precise cursed energy control.</i>

20:00.699 --> 20:03.869
<i>You can’t predict the attack
until the very last moment.</i>

20:05.829 --> 20:07.205
<i>But for him,</i>

20:07.206 --> 20:11.459
<i>cursed energy is constantly rising
from his entire body, including the sword.</i>

20:11.460 --> 20:14.712
<i>It's not even about
reading movements anymore.</i>

20:14.713 --> 20:17.215
<i>Every attack can be a finishing blow,</i>

20:17.216 --> 20:20.385
<i>and he can minimize all damage to him.</i>

20:20.969 --> 20:22.137
<i>I’ll leave the rest to you.</i>

20:22.971 --> 20:26.642
Sorry, but I’m not dying just yet.

20:34.441 --> 20:35.775
<i>Depending on the type,</i>

20:35.776 --> 20:38.487
some sorcerers train
with weapon handling as their foundation.

20:40.072 --> 20:44.408
I don’t want cursed energy control
to get neglected either.

20:44.409 --> 20:46.828
<i>This kind of thing
might still be too early for you.</i>

20:47.996 --> 20:49.748
<i>Slaughter Demon is emergency treatment.</i>

20:51.166 --> 20:52.709
<i>I never learned that!</i>

20:54.753 --> 20:55.670
<i>His consciousness…</i>

20:55.671 --> 20:57.047
You’re focusing too much on the sword.

21:05.097 --> 21:07.932
<i>My sword broke. Well, I guess so.</i>

21:07.933 --> 21:09.892
<i>He is Mr. Gojo's student.</i>

21:09.893 --> 21:12.062
Guess it wasn’t going to be easy.

21:12.688 --> 21:15.481
<i>The wound is deep,
but my organs aren’t out.</i>

21:15.482 --> 21:18.068
<i>Now, we’re both unarmed.
I can still fight.</i>

21:23.657 --> 21:26.743
What are you doing?

21:29.830 --> 21:32.708
We’re just playing. Rika…

21:33.667 --> 21:35.918
<i>Rika? What is this thing?</i>

21:35.919 --> 21:38.588
<i>Shikigami? Where did this thing come from?</i>

21:40.299 --> 21:41.466
Hold him down.

21:42.301 --> 21:43.218
<i>I can’t move…</i>

21:45.804 --> 21:47.472
<i>What kind of strength is this?</i>

21:54.855 --> 21:56.315
I’m sorry,

22:02.904 --> 22:04.406
Itadori.

23:41.503 --> 23:43.754
<i>A big brother who’s worse than
his little brother has no reason to exist.</i>

23:43.755 --> 23:46.715
<i>I can’t understand
someone who couldn’t love their siblings.</i>

23:46.716 --> 23:48.801
<i>-Itadori’s death…
- Maybe all the distortions</i>

23:48.802 --> 23:50.469
<i>started back then.</i>

23:50.470 --> 23:53.180
<i>- Don’t look down on me.
- Start by saving me.</i>

23:53.181 --> 23:55.432
<i>Tsumiki has been dragged
into the Culling Game too.</i>

23:55.433 --> 23:55.934
‎NEXT EPISODE
